item.title: Biden to urge Trump 'not walk away from Ukraine' in key meeting
item.description: President-elect Donald Trump and President Joe Biden are scheduled to meet on Wednesday to discuss critical domestic and international policy matters, including the ongoing war in Ukraine. National security adviser Jake Sullivan revealed that Biden will emphasize the importance of a smooth power transition and advocate for continued support for Ukraine, a stance opposed by Trump and some Republican lawmakers.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: New York Parks employee dies while battling wildfire in Orange Country
item.description: An 18-year-old New York parks employee tragically lost his life to a falling tree while combating a wildfire raging along the New York-New Jersey border. This fire, one of several sparked by dry conditions, has consumed thousands of acres, prompting air quality warnings in both states. Firefighters are battling to contain the blaze, which threatens numerous structures.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: ​'I wish him...': Nikki Haley responds to her exclusion from Trump's administration
item.description: Former US Ambassador Nikki Haley and former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will not be part of Donald Trump's new administration, as confirmed by Trump himself. Despite this, Haley expressed her well wishes for Trump's success in her statement on X. Both were considered potential candidates for cabinet positions.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'A pragmatic way': Vivek Ramaswamy backs Trump's mass deportation plans
item.description: Vivek Ramaswamy, a staunch supporter of Donald Trump, has voiced his support for the proposed mass deportation plan, deeming it a practical solution aligned with public sentiment. He emphasized prioritizing the deportation of illegal immigrants convicted of crimes, which he believes would constitute the most extensive deportation in history.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Amsterdam police use hologram to solve murder mystery of young sex worker
item.description: Amsterdam police are using a hologram of Bernadett Szabó, a Hungarian sex worker murdered in 2009, to seek new leads in her unsolved case. Szabó, a young mother, was found stabbed to death in her Red Light District workroom. Despite an extensive investigation, her killer remains unidentified.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Masked man tries to snatch Jewish child from father's arms in New York
item.description: A man attempted to kidnap a six-year-old boy from his father on a Brooklyn sidewalk on Saturday afternoon. The incident, caught on video, shows the suspect grabbing the child and lifting him into the air before the father intervened. The suspect fled and no injuries were reported. Police are investigating the incident.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: YouTuber Johnny Somali apologises for kissing statue honoring Korean wartime victims
item.description: American YouTuber Johnny Somali faces backlash and a police investigation in South Korea after posting a video of himself kissing a statue honoring Korean victims of wartime sexual slavery. Despite issuing an apology, Somali's sincerity is questioned due to other controversial content remaining on his social media accounts.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: '​Not true': Ella Emhoff denies mental breakdown after stepmom Harris' presidential loss
item.description: Ella Emhoff, stepdaughter of Kamala Harris, refuted rumors about her mental health on Instagram, denying claims of hospitalization after Harris's election loss. Emhoff addressed the speculation sparked by her emotional response during Harris's concession speech, emphasizing the normalcy of expressing emotions and advocating for mental health awareness.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Fire breaks out on Japan navy ship, cause under investigation
item.description: A fire erupted in the engine room of the Japanese minesweeper Ukushima, prompting the evacuation of its crew. One crew member is currently missing, and another was hospitalized due to smoke inhalation. The cause of the fire, which occurred off the coast of Kyushu, remains under investigation. Efforts to extinguish the fire are ongoing.

item.title: Seven deadly wins: Trump takes Arizona for a clean sweep of the battleground states
item.description: Donald Trump has won the 2024 presidential election, securing victories in all seven battleground states and achieving 312 electoral votes. Despite facing a financially stronger opponent in Kamala Harris, Trump's triumph has raised concerns among Democrats and sparked discussions about potential policy shifts during his upcoming term.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: King Charles leads silence for UK war dead as Kate returns to public life
item.description: King Charles III, joined by dignitaries and the public, led Britain's Remembrance Sunday service, honoring fallen soldiers. Catherine, Princess of Wales, marked her return to royal duties following cancer treatment, attending the service and a commemorative concert alongside Prince William. Both Charles and Catherine have been undergoing treatment for cancer diagnoses this year.

item.title: 'Those responsible for indiscriminate killings': Bangladesh to seek Interpol 'red notices' for fugitive Hasina loyalists
item.description: Bangladesh said Sunday it would request an Interpol "red notice" alert for fugitive leaders of the ousted regime of former prime minister Sheikh Hasina, who was toppled in a revolution in August. Red notices issued by the global police body alert law enforcement agencies worldwide about fugitives.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Palestinian hospital official says 17 killed in Israeli strike on northern Gaza
item.description: An Israeli airstrike on a home sheltering displaced Palestinians in the Jabaliya refugee camp in the northern Gaza Strip resulted in at least 17 fatalities, including nine women, as confirmed by Dr. Fadel Naim, director of Al-Ahly Hospital. Rescue operations are ongoing, suggesting a potential increase in the death toll. The Israeli military has not issued a statement yet.

item.title: Watch: Old video of Pakistan girl claiming to be Trump's daughter goes viral
item.description: A 2018 video of a Pakistani woman claiming to be Donald Trump's daughter has resurfaced online after his 2024 election victory. Speaking in Urdu, the woman alleges mistreatment by Melania Trump and claims Trump doubted her mother's parenting. Though initially unnoticed, the video is now being widely shared on social media.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Did he drug me too?': Why Gisèle Pelicot's daughter fears she was also victimised
item.description: Gisèle Pelicot, 72, accused her ex-husband, Dominique, of drugging and orchestrating her rape by numerous men over a decade. Their daughter, Caroline Darian, discovered she might also be a victim after police found photos of her in evidence. Dominique admitted to drugging Gisèle and filming her assaults but denies abusing Darian.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Canada reports first human case of bird flu after teen tests positive
item.description: A teenager in British Columbia, Canada, has contracted the H5 strain of bird flu, marking the country's first confirmed human case. Health officials are investigating the source of the infection, suspecting animal-to-human transmission. While human cases are rare, the virus's ability to jump species raises concerns about its potential to mutate and spread among humans.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Iran man charged with plotting Trump assassination tasked with targeting Israeli tourists in Sri Lanka: US
item.description: The FBI has charged Iranian national and Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps operative Farhad Shakeri with plotting to assassinate former President Donald Trump and orchestrate attacks on Israeli tourists in Sri Lanka. Shakeri, currently a fugitive believed to be in Tehran, was allegedly tasked with organizing a mass shooting in October 2024.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: FEMA fires employee for instructing hurricane relief team 'to skip houses advertising Trump'
item.description: A FEMA staff member was fired for instructing disaster response teams in Florida to avoid homes displaying pro-Trump signs following Hurricane Milton. FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell condemned the action, deeming it a violation of the agency's core values. An investigation is underway, and Florida Governor Ron DeSantis has launched a state-level inquiry into the incident.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Putin signs treaty with North Korea, strengthening military ties amid Ukraine conflict
item.description: Russia and North Korea have formalized a strategic partnership, including a mutual defense agreement. The treaty, ratified by Putin, follows reports of North Korean arms supplies to Russia and the deployment of North Korean troops to Ukraine. This development has raised concerns among Western nations, particularly as Ukrainian forces face mounting pressure from a renewed Russian offensive.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pakistan man stages kidnapping after killing son; arrested
item.description: A man in Lahore, Pakistan, was arrested for allegedly murdering his seven-year-old son and staging a kidnapping. The child's body was found buried at their residence. In other incidents, a woman suffered severe burns after her husband allegedly threw acid on her, and a man killed his wife and seven children due to financial hardship.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
